The "estr.h" header file defines:

* utob, for printing values as strings of "0"s and "1"s
* btou, for converting a string of "0"s and "1"s to a value
* revstr, to reverse the contents of a string in place (converts big to little endian)
* strnlen, for environments which only have strlen

